  "final_answer": "Heena is associated with several chemical compounds, including copper and ethanol, which are linked to various drugs. Some potential drug alternatives to Heena include Kogenate FS, which has a strong link with copper, and Alkeran (melphalan), which has a strong link with ethanol. Other potential alternatives include Sulfamoxole + Trimethoprim Veterinary Injectable Solution, Vincristine Sulfate Injection, and Dihydroergotamine Mesylate Drops, all of which have links with ethanol. However, it's essential to note that the comparison data is limited, and the alignment scores are relatively low, indicating uncertainty in the comparisons.\n\nThe links between the chemical compounds in Heena and the drug equivalents are as follows: copper has a strong link with Kogenate FS and a likely link with Copper Sulfate Additive Injection, while ethanol has a strong link with several drugs, including Alkeran (melphalan) and Dihydroergotamine Mesylate Drops.\n\nPlease consult a healthcare professional before using any of these drugs, as the information provided is based on limited data and may not be comprehensive or up-to-date. Additionally, the safety and efficacy of these drugs may vary depending on individual circumstances, and a healthcare professional can provide personalized guidance and recommendations.",
